# Base Development Standards
# Single Source of Truth — all copilot configs reference this file
# Stack: DeepLocal Forge · Rust · Python · JS/TS · React · PHP · HTML/CSS

---

## Core Principles

1. **Baby steps, one task at a time** — never skip ahead or bundle unrelated changes
2. **Test-Driven Development** — write a failing test before writing implementation code
3. **Root cause before fix** — never patch a symptom without understanding its origin
4. **Explicit over implicit** — no magic, no silent assumptions in code or architecture
5. **Local-first** — no external API calls, no cloud dependencies in the core stack
6. **English only** — all code, comments, commit messages, and documentation in English
7. **Verify before declaring done** — run the full pipeline before closing a task

---

## Workflow: Spec-Driven Development

### For new projects (Model B — AI-assisted spec)

```
1. /enrich-us  <ticket>        → enrich user story with acceptance criteria
2. /plan-ticket <ticket>       → generate implementation plan in ai-specs/changes/
3. /develop    @<ticket>.md    → implement following the plan precisely
```

### For mature projects (Model A — human-written spec)

```
1. Human writes spec in ai-specs/specs/ (api-spec.yml, data-model.md)
2. /add ai-specs/specs/base-standards.mdc ARCHITECTURE.md CONSTRAINTS.md
3. /architect  [goal with reasoning budget]
4. /develop    [implement from architect output]
```

