## Critic Pass (mandatory after significant changes)

Run after any refactor, API change, or concurrency modification:

```
/ask
Critically review the last code modification.
For each issue found, use exactly this format:

Bug: <one-line description>
File: <filename>
Line: <line number or range>
Explanation: <why it is a problem>
Fix: <concrete suggestion>

Focus on: hidden bugs, performance regressions, incorrect ownership/lifetime
assumptions (Rust), edge cases not covered, violations of CONSTRAINTS.md.
If no issues found, respond only: "No issues found."
```

| Change type                        | Critic Pass |
|------------------------------------|-------------|
| Formatting, rename, comments       | Not needed  |
| New function with defined signature | Recommended |
| Module refactor or public API       | Mandatory   |
| Concurrency logic change           | Mandatory   |
| Error handling modification        | Mandatory   |
